()Custom class kya hai kya karta hai?
--Custom.class = context ko batata hai ki Custom type ka object fetch karo (DB se).

🔹 Custom.class kya hai?
👉 Custom.class = Java class reference hai (type batane ke liye)
📌 Simple line:-
Context ko batata hai ki kis type ka object fetch karna hai.
code:-
Custom custom = context.getObjectByName(Custom.class, "MyConfig");
👉 Yaha:-
Custom.class → bol raha hai:-
“Custom type ka object lao”

🔥store hota hai db me:-
👉 Ye internally karta hai:-
Custom.class → spt_custom table
Identity.class → spt_identity table

🔹 Code Concept:-
Custom custom = context.getObjectByName(Custom.class, "Mapping_AD_Restricted_Groups");
🧠 Kya ho raha hai yaha?
👉 Ye line:-
Custom object ko DB se fetch kar rahi hai by name.

🔸 "Mapping_AD_Restricted_Groups"
👉 Object ka naam hai
👉 Jo SailPoint me already stored hai.

⚔️ Real Comparison:-
✔️ Correct:-
context.getObjectByName(Custom.class, "MyConfig");
❌ Galat:-
context.getObjectByName(Identity.class, "MyConfig");
👉 Kyunki:-
"MyConfig" Custom object hai, Identity nahi.
---------------------------------------------
()custom.class:-
Ye XML SailPoint ka ek Custom Object define karta hai jo ek configurable data store ki tarah kaam karta hai,
jisme organization ke sensitive AD groups ke liye risk levels aur access governance rules
(approval, approver, auto revoke) structured format me store kiye jate hain,
taki runtime pe system in rules ke basis pe automated aur secure decision le sake.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<!DOCTYPE Custom PUBLIC "sailpoint.dtd" "sailpoint.dtd">
<Custom name="Mapping_AD_Restricted_Groups">
  <Description>This object stores the mapping of highly restricted AD groups to their risk levels and required approver workgroups.</Description>
  <Attributes>
    
	<Map>
      <entry key="Domain Admins" value="Critical_Risk"/>
      <entry key="Enterprise Admins" value="Critical_Risk"/>
      <entry key="Account Operators" value="High_Risk"/>
      
      <entry key="VPN_External_Access">
        <value>
          <Map>
            <entry key="requiresApproval" value="true"/>
            <entry key="approverWorkgroup" value="Network_Security_Team"/>
            <entry key="autoRevokeDays" value="30"/>
          </Map>
        </value>
      </entry>

      <entry key="AWS_Production_ReadWrite">
        <value>
          <Map>
            <entry key="requiresApproval" value="true"/>
            <entry key="approverWorkgroup" value="Cloud_Admin_Team"/>
            <entry key="autoRevokeDays" value="15"/>
          </Map>
        </value>
      </entry>
    </Map>
  
  
  </Attributes>
</Custom>
////////////*
()<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
👉 Standard XML declaration
👉 Batata hai:-
XML version
encoding (UTF-8)
-------------------------------------------------------
()🔥 🔹 2️⃣ DOCTYPE:-
<!DOCTYPE Custom PUBLIC "sailpoint.dtd" "sailpoint.dtd">
👉 Bada explanation:-
Ye line define karti hai ki:-
👉 “Ye XML ek valid SailPoint Custom object hai”
sailpoint.dtd:-
Ye ek rulebook (schema) hai
Jo define karta hai:-
kaunse tags allowed hain
kaunsa structure valid hai
👉 Iska role:-
XML validation
Structure correctness ensure karna

👉 Agar structure galat hua:-
➡ SailPoint load nahi karega
------------------------------------------------------------------
()🔥 🔹 <Custom> tag:-
<Custom name="Mapping_AD_Restricted_Groups">
Main object hai SailPoint ka
🔹 name:-
👉 Object ka naam:-
Mapping_AD_Restricted_Groups
👉 Is naam se:-
context.getObject(Custom.class, "Mapping_AD_Restricted_Groups");
se fetch kar sakte ho.Ye ek named configuration container hai jisme specific business logic data store hai.
-------------------------------------------------------------------
()🔥 🔹 <Description>:-
<Description>This object stores the mapping of highly restricted AD groups...</Description>
Human-readable description hai
👉 Batata hai:-
Ye object kis kaam ke liye bana hai
👉 System use nahi karta logic me
👉 Sirf documentation / understanding ke liye.
-----------------------------------------------------
🔥 🔹 5️⃣ <Attributes>
<Attributes>:-
👉 Bada explanation:-
Ye ek data container tag hai
Custom object ke andar jo bhi actual data hota hai, wo isi ke andar hota hai
👉 SailPoint internally:-
Isko Map structure me convert karta hai
👉 Matlab:-
Ye logical boundary hai jahan se actual configuration start hota hai.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
🔥 🔹 6️⃣ <Map> (CORE ENGINE ⚡):-
👉 Bada explanation:-
Ye sabse important tag hai
Ye represent karta hai:-
👉 Java Map (key-value structure)
👉 Iska kaam:-
Data ko structured form me store karna
Fast lookup provide karna
👉 Structure:-
key → value
👉 Ye allow karta hai:-
simple values
complex nested structures
----------------------------------
🔥 🔹 7️⃣ <entry> (Data Unit):-
<entry key="Domain Admins" value="Critical_Risk"/>
👉 Bada explanation:-
Ye ek single data record represent karta hai
Har entry ek mapping define karti hai.
👉 Real meaning:-
Ek rule define ho raha hai: “Is group ka risk kya hai”
-------------------------------------------
<entry key="Domain Admins" value="Critical_Risk"/>
<entry key="Enterprise Admins" value="Critical_Risk"/>
<entry key="Account Operators" value="High_Risk"/>
👉 Deep explanation:-
Ye groups highly privileged hain
System ko bataya ja raha hai:-
kaunsa group kitna dangerous hai.

🔥 System kya karega:-
👉 Jab koi user ye group maangega:-
System bolega → HIGH ALERT 🚨
Extra approval ya restriction lagega
-----------------------------------------
🔥 🔹 8️⃣ <value> (Wrapper for Complex Data):-
<value>
  <Map>
👉 Bada explanation:-
Jab value simple string nahi hoti
Tab <value> tag use hota hai
👉 Ye allow karta hai:-
nested structure
multiple parameters store karna
-----------------------------------------
🔥 🔹 1️⃣ <value> kyun use kiya?
👉 Simple case:-
<entry key="Domain Admins" value="Critical_Risk"/>
👉 Yaha:-
value = ek simple string hai
➡ isliye direct value="..." likh diya.

👉 Complex case:-
<entry key="VPN_External_Access">
  <value>
    <Map>...</Map>
  </value>
</entry>
👉 Yaha:-
value simple string nahi hai ❌
multiple settings hain ✔
👉 Isliye <value> tag use kiya.
<value> ek wrapper hai jo complex data (jaise Map, List, object) ko hold karta hai.
------------------------------------
🔥 🔹 2️⃣ Ye 3 entries ka matlab kya hai?
<entry key="requiresApproval" value="true"/>
<entry key="approverWorkgroup" value="Network_Security_Team"/>
<entry key="autoRevokeDays" value="30"/>

🔹 1️⃣ requiresApproval = true:-
Ye ek boolean flag hai jo system ko batata hai:-
➡ “User ko direct access mat do”
➡ “Pehle approval lo”

🔹 2️⃣ approverWorkgroup = Network_Security_Team:-
Ye batata hai kaun approve karega
🔥 Real execution:-
String approver = "Network_Security_Team";
sendApprovalRequest(approver);
👉 System:-
request us group ko bhejta hai
wo approve/reject karte hain

🔹 3️⃣ autoRevokeDays = 30:-
Ye batata hai access kitne din valid rahega
🔥 Real execution:-
scheduleRevoke(user, access, 30);
👉 System:-
30 din baad access hata deta hai.


-----------------------------------------------
👉 “kya ye system ko bolta hai ya khud kuch karta hai?”
👉 Direct answer:-
❌ Ye khud kuch nahi karta
✔ Ye sirf configuration / instruction deta hai

🔥 🔹 Actual kaam kaun karta hai?
Rules (Beanshell)
Workflows
Provisioning engine
SailPoint logic

🔥 Flow samajh (VERY IMPORTANT):-
Custom Object (ye XML)
        ↓
System read karta hai
        ↓
Rule / Workflow use karta hai
        ↓
Actual action hota hai
----------------------------------------
